Don't move.

682
00:31:46,320 --> 00:31:46,900
Don't move.

683
00:31:46,910 --> 00:31:47,990
Right, squat lower.

684
00:31:48,010 --> 00:31:48,950
Lower yourself a bit more.

685
00:31:48,970 --> 00:31:52,230
Aizhen, do you find training hard?

686
00:31:52,330 --> 00:31:55,050
It is, but it's okay.

687
00:31:55,540 --> 00:31:59,110
Dad, tell me his story.

688
00:32:01,580 --> 00:32:02,430
You brat,

689
00:32:02,650 --> 00:32:03,950
slacking off again, aren't you?

690
00:32:03,970 --> 00:32:05,170
Come on, come on.

691
00:32:05,190 --> 00:32:06,510
I'll beat you up.

692
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:09,510
Come on.

693
00:32:24,950 --> 00:32:27,390
Dad, does he know about me?

694
00:32:31,180 --> 00:32:33,110
I've asked so many times already.

695
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:34,260
I can't help it.

696
00:32:34,390 --> 00:32:36,730
I really wish he could know about me,

697
00:32:36,750 --> 00:32:38,750
just like I know about him.

698
00:32:38,870 --> 00:32:39,670
Hurry up.

699
00:32:39,750 --> 00:32:42,920
I want to hear more stories about him.

700
00:33:09,950 --> 00:33:12,520
This is the first weapon he made.

701
00:33:12,900 --> 00:33:15,270
I've secretly taken it out

702
00:33:15,620 --> 00:33:16,510
to give it to you.

703
00:33:17,610 --> 00:33:18,470
Later,

704
00:33:18,880 --> 00:33:21,430
you can find a sheath that fits

705
00:33:21,620 --> 00:33:22,750
and encase it properly.

706
00:33:23,070 --> 00:33:24,590
I'll make one myself.

707
00:33:24,950 --> 00:33:25,790
Aizhen,

708
00:33:26,070 --> 00:33:27,470
leaving you here alone,

709
00:33:28,280 --> 00:33:29,270
you've suffered.

710
00:33:30,810 --> 00:33:32,030
I have no choice.

711
00:33:32,180 --> 00:33:33,230
It's okay.

712
00:33:33,410 --> 00:33:36,590
I feel as if both of you are always here with me.

713
00:33:36,770 --> 00:33:39,850
When I'm sad, I think of you both.

714
00:33:40,320 --> 00:33:43,150
It makes life a little easier to bear.

715
00:33:45,130 --> 00:33:46,110
Qing Cai.

716
00:33:47,460 --> 00:33:50,310
Can you... hug me?

717
00:33:53,190 --> 00:33:54,140
Just for once.

718
00:33:59,080 --> 00:34:00,030
Hurry up.

719
00:34:07,640 --> 00:34:09,070
Don't be so rigid.

720
00:34:09,850 --> 00:34:10,830
Be gentler.

721
00:34:18,199 --> 00:34:18,989
Yes.

722
00:34:19,340 --> 00:34:20,310
Just like this.

723
00:34:21,739 --> 00:34:22,830
For me...

724
00:34:25,330 --> 00:34:26,480
this is enough.

725
00:34:27,690 --> 00:34:28,949
Actually, I know.

726
00:34:30,590 --> 00:34:32,750
You're deliberately acting recklessly.

727
00:34:35,130 --> 00:34:35,989
Nonsense.

728
00:34:36,949 --> 00:34:38,110
I'm not reckless at all.

729
00:34:38,449 --> 00:34:39,750
I'm incredibly gentle.

730
00:34:43,540 --> 00:34:45,350
Stop teasing me.

731
00:34:49,650 --> 00:34:50,870
Then in the future...

732
00:34:53,600 --> 00:34:55,550
will you still be my friend?

733
00:34:57,380 --> 00:34:58,230
Of course.

734
00:35:00,210 --> 00:35:02,190
I'll treat you like my own big sister.

735
00:35:02,720 --> 00:35:04,390
What "big sister"?

736
00:35:05,390 --> 00:35:08,150
If you can't find the right words, just stay silent.

737
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:09,910
Be quiet.

738
00:35:17,140 --> 00:35:18,070
Thank you.

739
00:35:47,580 --> 00:35:48,830
Why are you crying?

740
00:35:49,950 --> 00:35:51,110
You're so dramatic.

741
00:36:01,380 --> 00:36:02,230
Let's drink.

742
00:36:11,390 --> 00:36:13,430
What are you staring at? You drink too.

743
00:36:14,820 --> 00:36:15,630
Okay.

744
00:36:24,180 --> 00:36:28,630
I didn't expect to actually taste the richness of this wine.

745
00:36:29,690 --> 00:36:30,430
Give it to me.

746
00:37:24,980 --> 00:37:29,990
May I be like the stars, and you the moon,

747
00:37:30,880 --> 00:37:36,870
glimmering every night and illuminating each other.

748
00:37:37,800 --> 00:37:42,830
Who knew we couldn't tie the knot,

749
00:37:44,910 --> 00:37:52,470
turning into a thousand longings instead?

750
00:38:09,950 --> 00:38:16,630
The breeze carries the yearnings to distant places;

751
00:38:17,930 --> 00:38:23,790
The flute's mournful notes linger under the bright moon.

752
00:38:25,490 --> 00:38:30,870
Worn and withered... from yearning for you;

753
00:38:32,270 --> 00:38:40,550
Only to meet and drink... making the past fade away.

754
00:39:22,250 --> 00:39:24,430
Come on, how are you this drunk

755
00:39:24,540 --> 00:39:26,350
from just a bit of wine?

756
00:39:29,300 --> 00:39:30,510
Zhang Fang!

757
00:39:34,840 --> 00:39:37,350
You... you don't understand.

758
00:39:38,180 --> 00:39:39,430
You don't understand.

759
00:39:40,910 --> 00:39:41,870
You don't understand.

760
00:39:42,290 --> 00:39:43,630
You don't understand.

761
00:39:43,790 --> 00:39:44,550
Don't understand.

762
00:40:30,900 --> 00:40:32,590
I'm really puzzled.

763
00:40:33,870 --> 00:40:36,390
Who on earth are these mysterious girls

764
00:40:36,650 --> 00:40:39,070
that have turned you two into

765
00:40:39,420 --> 00:40:42,230
such a mess?

766
00:40:43,680 --> 00:40:44,430
Alright.

767
00:40:45,780 --> 00:40:47,630
I'd like to see for myself.

768
00:41:16,770 --> 00:41:18,150
You haven't slept all night?

769
00:41:19,400 --> 00:41:22,150
I've been drifting in and out of sleep for a while.

770
00:41:24,360 --> 00:41:25,710
Do you want to go inside and catch up on some sleep?

771
00:41:33,880 --> 00:41:35,150
About yesterday...

772
00:41:36,430 --> 00:41:37,390
I'm sorry.

773
00:41:39,630 --> 00:41:41,430
I couldn't control my emotions.

774
00:41:41,790 --> 00:41:43,390
I hope I didn't cause you any trouble.

775
00:41:44,350 --> 00:41:45,110
You would never.

776
00:41:49,990 --> 00:41:51,990
You don't need to worry about me. I'm fine.

777
00:41:52,700 --> 00:41:53,710
Besides,

778
00:41:54,340 --> 00:41:55,470
now is not the time to talk about

779
00:41:55,470 --> 00:41:56,670
love or emotions.

780
00:41:57,770 --> 00:41:58,630
Well...

781
00:41:58,870 --> 00:42:00,750
I... I didn't mean it like that.

782
00:42:02,610 --> 00:42:03,840
I didn't mean it that way either.

783
00:42:04,970 --> 00:42:06,030
We're still friends.

784
00:42:13,740 --> 00:42:15,270
You, the heir to the throne...

785
00:42:17,330 --> 00:42:18,190
No.

786
00:42:19,020 --> 00:42:20,470
You, who's going to be the Emperor,

787
00:42:21,310 --> 00:42:23,190
can't be friends with commoners, right?

788
00:42:26,470 --> 00:42:27,310
It's okay.

789
00:42:28,120 --> 00:42:29,880
I don't want to be friends with

790
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:30,550
someone of your status either.

791
00:42:32,090 --> 00:42:34,310
No, I... I...

792
00:42:34,330 --> 00:42:36,190
I didn't mean that I didn't want to be friends with you.

793
00:42:36,470 --> 00:42:38,670
And I don't care about that status at all.

794
00:42:44,950 --> 00:42:46,280
But for me,

795
00:42:46,910 --> 00:42:49,310
I'm very happy, of course,

796
00:42:49,790 --> 00:42:51,150
to have a true friend to confide in.

797
00:42:54,260 --> 00:42:55,550
What I want to say is

798
00:42:55,640 --> 00:42:57,000
that I don't think the two of us

799
00:42:57,020 --> 00:42:58,350
need to be friends.

800
00:42:59,950 --> 00:43:00,710
No, I mean...

801
00:43:00,790 --> 00:43:01,630
I... I... I...

802
00:43:01,650 --> 00:43:02,990
What I'm trying to say is...

803
00:43:03,830 --> 00:43:05,540
there's something... something between us...

804
00:43:05,570 --> 00:43:06,710
What are you talking about?

805
00:43:07,770 --> 00:43:09,150
You're not making any sense.

806
00:43:12,970 --> 00:43:14,510
I'm just an idiot.

807
00:43:15,200 --> 00:43:16,500
This bright daylight

808
00:43:17,250 --> 00:43:18,750
ruins the mood completely.

809
00:43:19,790 --> 00:43:21,790
What... what mood are you talking about?

810
00:43:22,100 --> 00:43:22,990
Stop talking nonsense.

811
00:43:22,990 --> 00:43:24,060
Go back to sleep.

812
00:43:24,090 --> 00:43:25,710
I told you to take a nap, but you wouldn't go.

813
00:43:25,940 --> 00:43:26,790
Go quickly.

814
00:43:27,370 --> 00:43:28,830
I don't understand what you're saying.

815
00:43:32,550 --> 00:43:34,990
Then... I'll go to sleep.

816
00:43:36,110 --> 00:43:38,120
O-Otherwise, it'll be too awkward.

817
00:43:52,160 --> 00:43:53,440
You're feeling awkward?

818
00:43:54,170 --> 00:43:55,350
I'm the one who should feel awkward.

819
00:43:57,380 --> 00:43:58,910
I don't even know what you're saying.

820
00:44:11,730 --> 00:44:12,790
Did I wake you up?

821
00:44:14,220 --> 00:44:15,310
I went to bed early.

822
00:44:15,620 --> 00:44:18,630
It was about time... to wake up anyway.

823
00:44:19,630 --> 00:44:21,110
I made a fool of myself in front of you yesterday.

824
00:44:24,420 --> 00:44:27,510
You're the one... he likes.

825
00:44:31,780 --> 00:44:32,950
So what?

826
00:44:33,850 --> 00:44:35,670
There are too many obstacles between us.

827
00:44:38,060 --> 00:44:39,070
Indeed, there are.

828
00:44:39,770 --> 00:44:40,670
But...

829
00:44:41,470 --> 00:44:44,950
is there any obstacle we can't overcome?

830
00:44:46,480 --> 00:44:47,710
In this world,

831
00:44:48,940 --> 00:44:51,070
there are many things that cannot be overcome.

832
00:44:53,500 --> 00:44:55,990
I can overcome all the difficulties.

833
00:44:56,150 --> 00:44:57,190
Just like now,

834
00:44:57,240 --> 00:45:01,110
I'm fighting against the unbeatable laziness!

835
00:45:04,000 --> 00:45:05,100
If...

836
00:45:06,510 --> 00:45:08,590
he could give up everything for you...

837
00:45:11,550 --> 00:45:13,100
are you worried

838
00:45:14,490 --> 00:45:15,750
that he wouldn't do it?

839
00:45:16,180 --> 00:45:16,910
No,

840
00:45:17,500 --> 00:45:18,400
what I'm worried about is

841
00:45:18,430 --> 00:45:20,660
that this matter is too broad and too complicated.

842
00:45:22,530 --> 00:45:24,230
I don't want him to make such a sacrifice.

843
00:45:25,960 --> 00:45:27,150
But sometimes,

844
00:45:28,370 --> 00:45:29,870
what's lost

845
00:45:31,310 --> 00:45:32,790
is lost forever.

846
00:45:32,810 --> 00:45:34,670
Still, I don't want him

847
00:45:35,240 --> 00:45:36,990
to let me cloud his judgment.

848
00:45:40,610 --> 00:45:41,870
Don't try to force matters.

849
00:45:44,860 --> 00:45:46,070
Let nature take its course.

850
00:45:51,470 --> 00:45:52,470
It shouldn't be like this.

851
00:45:53,720 --> 00:45:55,390
Why aren't you encouraging me more?

852
00:45:55,840 --> 00:45:57,150
If I succeed,

853
00:45:57,420 --> 00:45:59,190
the biggest beneficiaries of this

854
00:45:59,210 --> 00:46:00,270
would be you guys, wouldn't it?

855
00:46:01,880 --> 00:46:03,270
If we face everything

856
00:46:03,960 --> 00:46:05,390
with extreme attitudes,

857
00:46:06,530 --> 00:46:08,190
things might become more complicated.
